# Commit Message Template for Backend Refactor

# Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, perf, chore
# Scope: phase0, week1, week2, etc.
# Subject: Imperative mood, lowercase, no period, <50 chars

# Body: Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# - What changed
# - Why this approach
# - What problem it solves

# Footer:
# - References to issues/PRs
# - Breaking changes
# - Reviewed-by: Codex

# Example:
# refactor(week1): add DTO view classes for logical decoupling
#
# - Created SubtitleView, TimelineView, VideoView, NotesView
# - Added view methods to ContentService
# - Extracted pure functions for SRT formatting and status validation
#
# This implements ISP compliance by allowing services to depend only
# on relevant fields without requiring full ContentMetadata.
#
# Reviewed-by: Codex
# Co-authored-by: Claude Code (PM Agent)
